{"id":"2306.01838","submitter":"Daniel Perry","authors":"Daniel Perry","title":"Existence of length minimizers in homotopy classes of Lipschitz paths in\n  $\\mathbb{H}^1$","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.MG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We show that for any purely 2-unrectifiable metric space $M$, for example the\nHeisenberg group $\\mathbb{H}^1$ equipped with the Carnot-Carath\\'{e}odory\nmetric, every homotopy class $[\\alpha]$ of Lipschitz paths contains a length\nminimizing representative $\\alpha_\\infty$ that is unique up to\nreparametrization. The length minimizer $\\alpha_\\infty$ is the core of the\nhomotopy class $[\\alpha]$ in the sense that the image of $\\alpha_\\infty$ is a\nsubset of the image of any path contained in $[\\alpha]$. Furthermore, the\nexistence of length minimizers guarantees that only the trivial class in the\nfirst Lipschitz homotopy group of $M$ with a base point can be represented by a\nloop within each neighborhood of the base point. The results detailed here will\nbe used to define and prove properties of a universal Lipschitz path space over\n$\\mathbb{H}^1$ in a subsequent paper.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Jun 2023 18:00:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Jun 2023 14:25:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
