sing O+ concentrations, waves become more\ndamped in specific wavenumber regions. However, the inclusion of oxygen ions\nmay allow weakly damped KAW to effectively propagate at smaller wave-normal\nangles than in the electron-proton case, as suggested by observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Jun 2023 19:22:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-06"}
