ata taking\nand provide an updated limit for the $^{180m}$Ta half-life on the different\ndecay channels. With new limits up to 1.5 x $10^{19}$ years, we improved\nexisting limits by one to two orders of magnitude. This result is the most\nsensitive search for a single $\\beta$ and electron capture decay ever achieved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 3 Jun 2023 00:18:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-06"}
